text: {| |} The Yakovlev Yak-112 Filin (Owl) is a Russian/Soviet civil utility aircraft that first flew in 1992. It is an all-metal high-wing strut braced monoplane with fixed tricycle landing gear. == Specifications (Yak-112) == ==References== * ==External links== *Yaklovlev English page on Yak-112 Category:1990s Soviet and Russian civil utility aircraft Category:High-wing aircraft Category:Single-engined tractor aircraft Category:Aircraft first flown in 1992
